JO  - AMR
SP  - 837
EP  - 847
VL  - 10
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Climate has been viewed as a function of: (a) the organization's structure; (b) the organization's membership; and (c) more recently the memberships' efforts to understand the organization. The third view?interactionism?has been offered as a reconciliation of the objectivism of the first and the subjectivism of the second. The interactionist approach is extended here by a consideration of the roles of the workgroup, affect, corporate culture, symbolic management, and physical setting.
